  "text": "Lynn Hamilton, best known to TV audiences for work on Sanford and Son and The Waltons, has passed away at the age of 95. According to The Hollywood Reporter, Hamilton died June 19 of natural causes at her home in Chicago. Hamilton recurred throughout Sanford and Son’s six-season run; she appeared in 22 episodes across six seasons, between 1972 and 1977. She initially played Lamont’s landlady in Season 1, Episode 7, but was reintroduced just three weeks later as Fred’s girlfriend-turned-fiancée, registered nurse Donna Harris (aka “The Barracuda”). Hamilton \u0026 Red Foxx on Sanford and Son Everett Collection Between 1973 and 1981, Hamilton also recurred on CBS’ The Waltons, on which she played Verdie Grant Foster — a role she would later reprise in two made-for-TV movies: A Walton Thanksgiving Reunion (1993) and A Walton Easter (1997). Hamilton also starred on a pair of short-lived soap operas — as matriarch Vivian Potter on NBC’s Generations (1989-91), and as Cissie Johnson on the syndicated drama Dangerous Woman (1991-92). Additional small-screen roles included Cousin Georgia Anderson on Roots: The Next Generations (1979), Emma Johnson on 227 (1986-89) and Judge P. Fulton on The Practice (1997-2002). Film credits included Shadows (1959), Brother John (1971), Buck and the Preacher (1972), Lady Sings the Blues (1972), Leadbelly (1976) and Legal Eagles (1986).",
  "image": "https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton.jpg?w=650",
  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-alias=\"gutenberg-content__content\" data-social=\"true\" data-component=\"gutenberg-content\" data-template=\"article\" data-inner-width=\"content\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tvline.com/t/lynn-hamilton/\" id=\"auto-tag_lynn-hamilton\" data-tag=\"lynn-hamilton\"\u003eLynn Hamilton\u003c/a\u003e, best known to TV audiences for work on \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tvline.com/t/sanford-and-son/\" id=\"auto-tag_sanford-and-son\" data-tag=\"sanford-and-son\"\u003eSanford and Son\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e and \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://tvline.com/t/the-waltons/\" id=\"auto-tag_the-waltons\" data-tag=\"the-waltons\"\u003eThe Waltons\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e, has passed away at the age of 95. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAccording to \u003cem\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/lynn-hamilton-dead-sanford-and-son-waltons-1236296486/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/tv/tv-news/lynn-hamilton-dead-sanford-and-son-waltons-1236296486/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"\u003eThe Hollywood Reporter\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/em\u003e, Hamilton died June 19 of natural causes at her home in Chicago. \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHamilton recurred throughout \u003cem\u003eSanford and Son’\u003c/em\u003es six-season run; she appeared in 22 episodes across six seasons, between 1972 and 1977. She initially played Lamont’s landlady in Season 1, Episode 7, but was reintroduced just three weeks later as Fred’s girlfriend-turned-fiancée, registered nurse Donna Harris (aka “The Barracuda”).\n\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1240\" height=\"840\" src=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg 1240w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=200,135 200w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=300,203 300w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=768,520 768w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=1024,694 1024w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=148,100 148w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=600,406 600w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=276,187 276w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=1000,677 1000w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=369,250 369w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=244,165 244w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=1160,786 1160w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=443,300 443w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=140,95 140w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=59,40 59w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=50,34 50w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=1200,813 1200w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=41,28 41w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=248,168 248w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=497,337 497w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=996,675 996w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=295,200 295w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=590,400 590w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=1181,800 1181w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=37,25 37w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=221,150 221w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=886,600 886w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=150,102 150w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=110,75 110w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=285,193 285w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=320,217 320w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=640,434 640w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/lynn-hamilton-sanford-and-son.jpg?resize=800,542 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1240px) 100vw, 1240px\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eHamilton \u0026amp; Red Foxx on \u003cem\u003eSanford and Son\u003c/em\u003e \u003ccite\u003eEverett Collection\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eBetween 1973 and 1981, Hamilton also recurred on CBS’ \u003cem\u003eThe Waltons\u003c/em\u003e, on which she played Verdie Grant Foster — a role she would later reprise in two made-for-TV movies: \u003cem\u003eA Walton Thanksgiving Reunion\u003c/em\u003e (1993) and \u003cem\u003eA Walton Easter\u003c/em\u003e (1997).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eHamilton also starred on a pair of short-lived soap operas — as matriarch Vivian Potter on NBC’s \u003cem\u003eGenerations\u003c/em\u003e (1989-91), and as Cissie Johnson on the syndicated drama \u003cem\u003eDangerous Woman\u003c/em\u003e (1991-92).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eAdditional small-screen roles included Cousin Georgia Anderson on \u003cem\u003eRoots: The Next Generations\u003c/em\u003e (1979), Emma Johnson on \u003cem\u003e227\u003c/em\u003e (1986-89) and Judge P. Fulton on \u003cem\u003eThe Practice\u003c/em\u003e (1997-2002). Film credits included \u003cem\u003eShadows\u003c/em\u003e (1959), \u003cem\u003eBrother John\u003c/em\u003e (1971), \u003cem\u003eBuck and the Preacher\u003c/em\u003e (1972), \u003cem\u003eLady Sings the Blues \u003c/em\u003e(1972), \u003cem\u003eLeadbelly\u003c/em\u003e (1976) and \u003cem\u003eLegal Eagles\u003c/em\u003e (1986).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cdiv data-component=\"linked-gallery\"\u003e\u003cfigure data-component=\"image\" data-alias=\"\" data-ratio=\"threeByTwo\" data-round=\"false\"\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tv-stars-we-lost-2025-v5.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\" alt=\"TV Stars Who Died in 2025\" height=\"840\" width=\"1240\" srcset=\"https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tv-stars-we-lost-2025-v5.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1 1240w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tv-stars-we-lost-2025-v5.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=200%2C135 200w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tv-stars-we-lost-2025-v5.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=300%2C203 300w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tv-stars-we-lost-2025-v5.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=768%2C520 768w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tv-stars-we-lost-2025-v5.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=1024%2C694 1024w, https://tvline.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/tv-stars-we-lost-2025-v5.jpg?w=1240\u0026amp;h=840\u0026amp;crop=1\u0026amp;resize=148%2C